         <notesStmt>
            <note>One leaf missing after folio 130 and 168 respectively.  Folio 3 is a recent restoration.  Folios 1-2 and 186-187 are vellum. Several pages water-damaged.  First few leaves damaged, preserved on paper. </note>
            <note>Folios 1r-2v, 186r-187vand contain Deuteronomy, chapters 13:7-18, 15:13-16:15, 30:20-31:10: Hebrew text with the sublinear punctuation, Targum with the simple superlinear puntuation, and Sa'adia Gaon's Arabic version in Hebrew characters. Has masorah magna and parva.
								Daṿid ben Sa῾id: stamped, folio 109v. </note>
            <note type="relatedResource">
								Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.
							</note>
